d","–Female":"Deceased","1270–Male":"1270–Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","1125–1166":"1125–1166","1135–1166":"1135–1166","Abt 1150":"about 1150","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","1166":"1166","Abt 1270":"about 1270","1150":"1150","1270":"1270","Fauld, Diseworth, England":"Fauld, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","Fauld, Staffordshire, England":"Fauld, Staffordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Curzon","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Notre-Dame-de-Courson in Calvados, France, which was named with the Gallo-Roman personal name <i>Curtius</i> (from <i>curtus</i> ‘short’) + the locative suffix <i>-o</i>, genitive <i>-onis</i>. There is also a place called Curzon in Vendée, but this is not the source of the English surname."],"variants":[{"name":"Curson","meanings":["English (Norfolk): variant of   Curzon  ."]}]},{"name":"Jerome","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Vernacular form of the Greek name <i>Hieronymos</i>, derived from <i>hieros</i> ‘holy’ + <i>onoma</i> ‘name’.  St Jerome  (  <i>c.</i>342–420 ) was a citizen of the Eastern Roman Empire, who bore the Greek names Eusebios Hieronymos Sophronios; he was chiefly responsible for the translation into Latin of the Bible, the Vulgate. He also wrote many works of commentary and exposition on the Bible, and is regarded as one of the Doctors of the Church. The Greek form of the name was used occasionally in England; it is recorded in Nottinghamshire, for example, in the late 16th century. Both <i>Jerome</i> and <i>Jeronimus</i> are found in Yorkshire and elsewhere from that date onwards. The name was borne by the British writer  Jerome K. Jerome  (  1859–1927 ), the American songwriter  Jerome Kern  (  1885–1945 ), and the American ballet dancer and choreographer  Jerome Robbins  (  1918–98 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jerome Curzon was born about 1150, in Fauld, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Stephen Curzon, was 27 and his mother, Afuca Gudrødsen, was 15. He had at least 1 son with Amicia Mompesson. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"Abt 1150–":"umbes 1150–Surnud","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1125–1166":"1125–1166","1135–1166":"1135–1166","Abt 1150":"umbes 1150","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","1166":"1166","Abt 1270":"umbes 1270","1150":"1150","1270":"1270","Fauld, Diseworth, England":"Fauld, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Fauld, Staffordshire, England":"Fauld, Staffordshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1150–":"noin 1150–Kuollut","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1125–1166":"1125–1166","1135–1166":"1135–1166","Abt 1150":"noin 1150","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","1166":"1166","Abt 1270":"noin 1270","1150":"1150","1270":"1270","Fauld, Diseworth, England":"Fauld, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Fauld, Staffordshire, England":"Fauld, Staffordshire, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1150–":"environ 1150–Décédé","1150–Male":"1150–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1270–Male":"1270–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1125–1166":"1125–1166","1135–1166":"1135–1166","Abt 1150":"environ 1150","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","1166":"1166","Abt 1270":"environ 1270","1150":"1150","1270":"1270","Fauld, Diseworth, England":"Fauld, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Fauld, Staffordshire, England":"Fauld, Staffordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Jerome Curzon est né environ 1150, à Fauld, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Stephen Curzon, avait 27 ans et sa mère, Afuca Gudrødsen, avait 15 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Amicia Mompesson. Il est décédé dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"Abt 1150–":"um 1150–Verstorben","1150–Male":"1150–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1270–Male":"1270–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","11